Part D: Apply Wireshark Display Filters 
Display filters allow analysis of captured traffic without modifying the original capture. 
Protocol Filters 
Display Filter 
tcp 
udp 
Purpose 
Show only TCP packets 
Show only UDP packets 
icmp 
dns 
http 
Show only ICMP packets 
Show only DNS traffic 
Show only HTTP traffic 
IP Address Filters 
Display Filter 
ip.addr == Your_IP 
ip.src == 192.168.0.1 
Purpose 
Traffic to or from your system 
Packets from a specific source 
ip.dst == <Metasploitable_IP> Packets destined for Metasploitable 
Port Filters 
Display Filter Purpose 
tcp.port == 80 HTTP traffic 
tcp.port == 443 HTTPS traffic 
Packet Characteristics 
Display Filter 
frame.len > 1000 
tcp.flags.syn == 1 
Purpose 
Large packets 
TCP SYN packets 
tcp.analysis.retransmission TCP retransmissions 
Part E: Combined Filters 
Apply the following filters and observe the results. 
tcp and ip.addr == 192.168.1.1 
http or dns 
tcp.port == 80 and ip.src == Your_IP 
!(icmp) 
Part F: TCP Flag Analysis 
Display Filter 
tcp.flags.syn == 1 
tcp.flags.ack == 1 
Purpose 
SYN packets 
ACK packets 
tcp.flags.fin == 1 
tcp.flags.reset == 1 
Connection termination 
TCP Reset packets 
tcp.flags.syn == 1 && tcp.flags.ack == 1 SYN-ACK packets 
Part G: DNS Traffic Analysis 
Display Filter 
dns.flags.response == 0 
dns.flags.response == 1 
Purpose 
DNS queries 
DNS responses 
dns.qry.name contains "google" Queries containing "google" 
dns.time > 1 
Slow DNS responses 
Part H: IP Packet Analysis 
Display Filter 
ip.ttl < 10 
ip.flags.df == 1 
ip.len > 1000 
Purpose 
Low TTL packets 
Don't Fragment flag set 
Large IP packets 
ip.src == 192.168.1.10 && ip.dst == 8.8.8.8 Specific communication path 
Part I: String Matching Filters 
Search for specific strings within captured packet data. 
http contains "password" 
frame contains "admin" 
Record and analyze any observations. 
Part J: Nmap Scan Identification 
Use Wireshark to distinguish between different Nmap scan types. 
SYN Scan 
Filter: 
tcp.flags.syn == 1 && tcp.flags.ack == 0 
Connect Scan 
Filter: 
tcp.flags.syn == 1 || tcp.flags.ack == 1 
UDP Scan 
Filter: 
udp 
OS Detection 
Filter: 
icmp or tcp.options 
Tasks 
1. Compare traffic generated by: 
o nmap -sS 
o nmap -sT 
o nmap -sU 
2. Count the number of packets generated by each scan. 
3. Identify which scan was fastest. 
4. Determine how Wireshark can distinguish between scan types. 
Part K: ARP Analysis 
Generate ARP traffic by pinging another host. 
Filter: 
arp 
Additional Filters: 
arp.opcode == 1 
arp.opcode == 2 
Tasks 
1. Identify ARP Requests. 
2. Identify ARP Replies. 
3. Determine MAC addresses of communicating devices. 
4. Explain ARP resolution. 
Part L: ICMP Analysis 
Generate ICMP traffic: 
ping <Metasploitable_IP> 
Filters: 
icmp 
icmp.type == 8 
icmp.type == 0 
Tasks 
1. Identify Echo Requests. 
2. Identify Echo Replies. 
3. Measure round-trip time. 
4. Determine packet size. 
Part M: Security and Credential Discovery 
Apply the following filters: 
